An area resident said many other dead bodies had in the past been discovered in the abandoned quarry.Area assistant chief said the body appeared to have been in the water for about one week. The decomposing body of an unknown man was Thursday found floating inside an abandoned flooded quarry at Kiambogo village, Nkubu area of Meru County.
Area residents said the man, who appears to be in his 30s, was spotted by passersby along the Nkubu-Mitunguu road late afternoon.
One resident who identified herself as Stella Gakii said the discovery of the body sent the entire village into panic.



