She said many other dead bodies had in the past been discovered in the abandoned quarry.
Appeal to government
Ms Gakii appealed to the government to fence off the deep pit to prevent people from easily accessing it, or drain the water out of it so that it can be covered with soil.
“The quarry was used and then left bare and water flooded it. Maybe there are other bodies trapped there," she said.
Kithunguri assistant chief Julius Kiogora said the body appeared to have been in the water for about one week since it had started decomposing.



